<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1434,1891]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,543,1434,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Taxonomic history and remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[552,759,1435,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[552,759,1435,1459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Micandra extrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Draudt" box="[971,1132,1435,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" refString="Draudt, M. (1919) Theclini F. In: A. Seitz (Ed). Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde, vol. 5. Die amerikanischen Tagfalter, Alfred Kernen, Stuttgart, pp. 744 - 812." type="book chapter" year="1919">
Draudt (
<number box="[1065,1123,1435,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="1919.0">1919</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as a form of 
<taxonomicName box="[1287,1361,1436,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Thecla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ion">
<emphasis box="[1287,1361,1436,1459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">M. ion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it was considered a valid species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Clench" box="[533,694,1471,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" refString="Clench, H. K. (1971) Two new hairstreaks from Mexico (Lepidoptera: Lycaenidae), Bulletin of the Allyn Museum, 3, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="1971">
Clench (
<number box="[627,685,1471,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Robbins" box="[748,916,1471,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" refString="Robbins, R. K. (1986) Evolution and identification of the New World hairstreak butterflies (Lycaenidae: Eumaeini): Eliot's Trichonis Section and Trichonis Hewitson, Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 40, 138 - 157." type="journal article" year="1986">
Robbins (
<number box="[856,916,1471,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="1986.2004">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Robbins" box="[926,987,1471,1495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" refString="Robbins, R. K. (2004) Checklist of Eumaeini. 98. Lycaenidae Theclinae, Eumaeini. 118 - 137 pp. In: Lamas, G., Checklist of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Part 4 A. Hesperioidea- Papilionoidea. Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. J. Heppner (Ed.) Scientific Publishers, Gainesville, 439 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
). Both species are extremely rare in collections making it difficult to assess variation. More than 
<number box="[798,826,1507,1531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" value="90.0">90</number>
years after its original description, a second specimen was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[341,451,1543,1567]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Colombia</collectingCountry>
by the biologist Ana Milena Mora; however, a male from 
<collectingCountry box="[1118,1211,1543,1567]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
is illustrated in this paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1434,1891]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1614,1639]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[330,539,1615,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[330,539,1615,1639]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Micandra extrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[811,966,1615,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis box="[811,966,1615,1639]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">M. platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1025,1101,1616,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Thecla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ion">
<emphasis box="[1025,1101,1616,1639]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">M. ion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the ventral wing pattern consistently distinguishes males as noted in the previous species account. Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1122,1250,1652,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="extrema">
<emphasis box="[1122,1250,1652,1675]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">M. extrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unknown or unrecognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1434,1891]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1722,1747]" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</emphasis>
This is the rarest 
<taxonomicName box="[559,669,1723,1747]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Micandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[559,669,1723,1747]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Micandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in 
<collectingCountry box="[798,911,1723,1747]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, known from a specimen recently collected in Nariño at 
<quantity box="[263,351,1759,1783]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
